ZH: 大脑是人类的重要器官。
EN: The brain is an important organ for humans.

ZH: 大脑可以控制我们的思维和行为。
EN: The brain can control our thoughts and actions.

ZH: 大脑是神经系统的核心部位。
EN: The brain is the core part of the nervous system.

ZH: 大脑可以帮助我们做出决策。
EN: The brain can help us make decisions.

ZH: 大脑接收并处理大量信息。
EN: The brain receives and processes a lot of information.

ZH: 大脑可以适应不同的情境。
EN: The brain can adapt to different situations.

ZH: 大脑可以结合直觉和逻辑思维。
EN: The brain can combine intuition and logical thinking.

ZH: 大脑的功能是非常复杂的。
EN: The functions of the brain are very complex.

ZH: 大脑需要不断锻炼才能保持活跃。
EN: The brain needs constant exercise to stay active.

ZH: 大脑的发育需要适当的营养。
EN: The development of the brain requires proper nourishment.

ZH: 大脑在睡眠时也会进行自我修复。
EN: The brain also undergoes self-repair during sleep.

ZH: 大脑的健康影响整个身体的运作。
EN: The health of the brain affects the functioning of the entire body.

ZH: 大脑不同部分的作用各不相同。
EN: The different parts of the brain have different functions.

ZH: 大脑的左右半球各负责不同的任务。
EN: The left and right hemispheres of the brain are responsible for different tasks.

ZH: 大脑的灰质和白质承担不同的功能。
EN: The gray matter and white matter of the brain have different functions.

ZH: 大脑可以在受伤后进行自我修复。
EN: The brain can undergo self-repair after injury.

ZH: 大脑的发育受遗传和环境的影响。
EN: The development of the brain is influenced by genetics and the environment.

ZH: 大脑的发展与学习密切相关。
EN: The development of the brain is closely related to learning.

ZH: 大脑的运作需要充足的氧气。
EN: The brain's functioning requires sufficient oxygen.

ZH: 大脑的发展可以受到损伤和疾病的影响。
EN: The development of the brain can be affected by damage and disease.
